==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Methysticin
<hw>Me*thys"ti*cin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A white, silky, crystalline substance extracted from the thick
rootstock of a species of pepper (<spn>Piper methysticum</spn>) of the
South Sea Islands; -- called also <altname>kanakin</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Metic</ent>⟦br⟧
